data.description:
On January 30th, 1948, Mahatma Gandhi, noted fighter for independence from British colonial rule in South Asia, was assassinated. 
Two years later, on February 15th, 1950, Nicholas B. Dirks, author of numerous books on the impact of British colonial rule in South Asia, was "born."
Conclude what you will.
